[DhtmlXQ_comment0]sg 20120914 1999 Slc Hong Zhi D Liu Dianzhong C45||C45 Central Cannon with 7th Pawn Advancement and Pawn ranked chariot vs Screen Horse Defense with Edge Cannon for Chariot Exchange Variation. ||ECCO:C45 ?????????????????||Jim: This annotated game was provided by Mr Chris Hankinson and is a perfect upload in view of my recent boards on openings by GM Liu Dianzhong. ||This match was played in January 1999 at Xingyang, Henan Provice. For those that do not know, Xiangyang was the place where the legendary Xiang Yu ?? did battle against his arch nemesis Liu Bang??. ||The event was the first ever Shaolin Autombile Cup and participants eligible to take part were of the highest caliber. Only the top 48 ranked players according to the ranking systems then were able to participate, and for those who could not make it, the next in ranked player would take the place. It was one of the toughest competition of its era.||The competition was held in two different stages. In the first stage, players were divided into 8 groups, playing a round robin each. The winner of the round robin would then be eligible for the second round whereby the players played in a double disqualification match to progress.||At the end of the day, the placings were as follows:||Champion: Lv Qin||1st Runner Up: Zhao Guorong, ||2nd Runner Up:Liu Dianzhong.||3rd to 8th place were Liu Dahua, Li Laiqun, Chen Xiaokun Xu Tianhong Huang Shiqing in that order. ||This game was played in the 3rd round in one of the groups. Hong Zhi (who would later become a GM also) was the second seed in that group and was a strong, respectable opponent. Hong is known for his rutheless attacking capabilitis, supreme precision in the calculation of his moves and had very strong midgame abilities. ||This was no doubt the most important match in that group and the winner would most likely proceed to the second round.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
